Key Match Events: Tim Pringle and Logan van Beek's three-wicket hauls backed up by Max O'Dowd's patient half-century got Netherlands over the line
Netherlands won by 6 wickets (with 8 balls remaining)
Nepal managed to bowl Netherlands out for 106 in 19.2 overs
Post-Match Reflections: Max O'Dowd expressed satisfaction with the team's performance and the win
Scott Edwards praised the bowlers' performance and the team's overall effort
Miscellaneous Highlights: Early-morning rain and overcast conditions delayed the toss by 30 minutes
Nepal fans made the stadium feel larger with their vocal support
Netherlands conceded only 4 runs in the first 15 balls of the powerplay
